{"body": "## Daily Internship Workflow\n\nEach morning, run through this checklist for the Internship Search space.\n\n### 1. Review open applications\n\nCall list_documents with type: application. For each doc:\n- If status is applied and it has been more than 7 days since updated_at, update status to follow-up via patch_frontmatter and add a note in the body.\n- If status is interview, check the body for a scheduled date. If the date has passed, update to post-interview.\n\n### 2. Log a daily summary\n\nWrite a document with type: log and status: done summarising what you reviewed:\n- Total applications by status\n- Any follow-ups flagged\n- Any interviews coming up in the next 7 days\n\nTitle it Daily Log \u2014 {today} and save to logs/daily-{today}.md.\n\n### 3. Search for new roles\n\nCall list_connections. If an n8n connection is present, call call_n8n_workflow with the connection id and payload { query: \"software engineering internship 2026\", space_id: \"jQKt7BgofxzI3JOB92uTL\" }. For each role returned, create an application document with status: new.\n\n### 4. Report\n\nReply with a short plain-text summary of what you did today."}
